This paper is likely to belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) as it introduces a new approach to reasoning over knowledge graphs using dependent type theory. It also involves the use of the Coq proof assistant, which is commonly used in the field of logic. Additionally, the paper touches on topics related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) such as explainability and automation. The use of RDF and SPARQL also suggests that this paper could be categorized under Databases (cs.DB) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the construction and querying of knowledge graphs, which could fall under the category of Software Engineering (cs.SE).
